                           <p>The right side and lower edge of a <material>white marble</material>
                              <objectType> panel-stele</objectType> without raised moulding (<height unit="metre">0.44</height> x <width unit="metre">0.325</width> x <depth unit="metre">0.165</depth>). The relief shows the lower part, from the chest downwards, of a <rs type="decoration">gladiator</rs> (a retiarius) wearing body armour, with bare legs, advancing to his left; he holds a short sword in his right hand and the staff of a trident (whose head is lost) in his left.</p>
